--- [RESPONSE] (12.2s) ---
### File Structure
```
NewsPortal/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── article_catalog.html
│   ├── article_details.html
│   ├── bookmarks.html
│   ├── comments.html
│   ├── write_comment.html
│   ├── trending.html
│   ├── category.html
│   └── search_results.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (optional thumbnails or icons)
│
└── data/
    ├── articles.txt
    ├── categories.txt
    ├── bookmarks.txt
    ├── comments.txt
    └── trending.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will handle routing, data reading/writing from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and rendering the HTML templates with the appropriate data. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic (including article management, bookmarks, comments, trending data, and search/filter functionality) will be implemented here.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the nine pages defined in the requirements. Each HTML file corresponds to one page and includes the specified elements with their IDs for frontend rendering and interaction.
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page layout.
  - `article_catalog.html`: Article catalog with search and filter.
  - `article_details.html`: Detailed article view with bookmark option.
  - `bookmarks.html`: Bookmarked articles list with read/remove options.
  - `comments.html`: Comments listing and filter.
  - `write_comment.html`: Form to submit new comments.
  - `trending.html`: Trending articles with time period filter.
  - `category.html`: Articles filtered by category with sorting.
  - `search_results.html`: Search results display.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS, JavaScript, and images.
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent UI styling.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, dynamic filtering).
  - `images/`: Optional folder for article thumbnails or icons if needed.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
  - `articles.txt`: Articles data.
  - `categories.txt`: Categories data.
  - `bookmarks.txt`: Bookmarks data.
  - `comments.txt`: Comments data.
  - `trending.txt`: Trending articles data.

This structure supports a clean separation of concerns, with a single backend file for simplicity, dedicated templates for each page, and organized static and data resources.
